<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29485>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Dorsal habitus of four Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Caverneleodes) wheeleri; B Eleodes (Eleodes) armatus C Eleodes (Eleodes) caudiferus D Eleodes (Eleodes) tribulus. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29485" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29486>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Dorsal habitus of four Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus B Eleodes (Melaneleodes) anthracinus C Eleodes (Melaneleodes) carbonarius D Eleodes (Tricheleodes) pilosus. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29486" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29487>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Lateral habitus of three Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Blapylis) nigropilosus B Eleodes (Caverneleodes) wheeleri C Eleodes (Eleodes) armatus. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29487" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29488>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Lateral habitus of three Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Eleodes) caudiferus B Eleodes (Eleodes) tribulus C Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29488" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29489>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Lateral habitus of three Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Melaneleodes) anthracinus B Eleodes (Melaneleodes) carbonarius C Eleodes (Tricheleodes) pilosus. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29489" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29490>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Lateral habitus of the head and thoracic segments of three Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Melaneleodes) anthracinus B Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus C Eleodes (Promus) subnitens. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29490" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29491>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Eleodes (Melaneleodes) anthracinus, epipharnyx. asp = anterior spines, msp = medial spines, mst = microsetae, pap = sensory papillae, tor = tormae. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29491" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29492>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Epipharynges of four Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Melaneleodes) carbonarius B Eleodes (Eleodes) armatus C Eleodes (Eleodes) hispilabris D Eleodes (Eleodes) tribulus. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29492" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29493>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Epipharynges of four Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus B Eleodes (Promus) goryi C Eleodes (Promus) subnitens D Eleodes (Tricheleodes) pilosus. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29493" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29494>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Ligulas of three Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Melaneleodes) carbonarius B Eleodes (Eleodes) armatus C Eleodes (Promus) goryi. Scale bars = 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29494" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29495>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Hypopharyngeal scleromes of two Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Melaneleodes) carbonarius B Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus. Scale bars = 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29495" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29496>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Abdominal sternites I and II for two Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Eleodes) caudiferus B Eleodes (Litheleodes) extricatus. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29496" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29497>
    dc:description "Figure 14. Pygidia of two Eleodes species: A Eleodes (Eleodes) hispilabris B Eleodes (Tricheleodes) pilosus. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29497" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

